Source: Newswire briefs [edited]
[A] Japan from Sanyo Shimbun 27 March 2003 [submitted & trans. by Shizuka
Shimura and Cherie McCown] [edited]
A man coming back from Taiwan was taken to hospital in Hiroshima Prefecture
and reported as a suspected case of SARS on 26 Mar 2003. According to the
Prefecture's investigation, the man went to Taiwan on 11 Mar 2003 and
returned to Japan on 25 Mar 2003. He had onset of fever (nearly 39 C),
radiographic examination of his chest revealed pneumonia and was admitted
to the hospital on 26 Mar 2003.
[To date there have been no official reports of suspected or probable cases
of SARS to WHO from Japan. This is the second newswire suggesting there
may be cases in Japan. More information from official sources would be
appreciated. - Mod.MPP]
